            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1637082368726-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>sweet pointed</strong> <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and finely dice</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock mix</strong>, <strong>ground turmeric </strong>and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>tomato paste</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) in 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1637082385346-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1637082385346-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1637082385346-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1637082385346-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1637082385346-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>diced</strong> <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until they've softened slightly</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1637082389790-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1637082389790-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1637082389790-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1637082389790-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1637082389790-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> white long grain rice</strong>, <strong>tomato stock </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the<strong> chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving – this is your <strong>spicy rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1637082395025-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1637082395025-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1637082395025-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1637082395025-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1637082395025-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>chipotle paste</strong>, <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>tomato paste</strong> with the juice of <strong>half </strong>your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> in a large mixing bowl</p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong>,<strong> </strong>then give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>peri peri sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1637082399784-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1637082399784-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
